      },
      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "When `perf_available` is true, `self.options.perf` is not always true.\r\n\r\nBy checking only for `perf_available` (which is set only if perf is actually active) you are also fixing an issue where if [`profile_with_perf`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/tree/master/test/functional#benchmarking-with-perf) is used, the directory still gets cleaned up, and therefore the perf data are lost.\r\n```suggestion\r\n            not (perf_available)\r\n```\r\nand also should check for `perf_available` instead of `self.options.perf` as part of the below conditional statement.",
      "commit_id" : "c0f468690b7994a8604a3d8f7ec30ebf3105dfb8",
      "created_at" : "2023-01-30T14:11:57Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -307,11 +307,12 @@ def shutdown(self):\n                 node.cleanup_on_exit = False\n             self.log.info(\"Note: bitcoinds were not stopped and may still be running\")\n \n+        perf_available = any(bool(node.perf_available) for node in self.nodes)\n         should_clean_up = (\n             not self.options.nocleanup and\n             not self.options.noshutdown and\n             self.success != TestStatus.FAILED and\n-            not self.options.perf\n+            not (self.options.perf and perf_available)",
